BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:C-qXCbgvNTEeNQHE53hFH
SUMMARY:Intro to Improv Eastside - Issaquah SUNDAYS
DTSTAMP:20260307T230149Z
DTSTART:20260308T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Discover improv in Issaquah. Build confidence\, meet new people
	\, and learn to create stories through fun\, supportive games and scene wo
	rk.\n\nLooking for a fun\, fresh way to connect with others\, spark creati
	vity\, and step out of the everyday routine? Welcome to Intro to Improv at
	 Unexpected Productions Improv School Eastside in Issaquah. Whether you ar
	e a working professional hoping to improve communication\, a creative soul
	 searching for a new outlet\, or someone simply wanting more laughter and 
	community in your week\, this class is the perfect place to begin. \n\nIn 
	this beginner-friendly course\, you will learn the foundational skills of 
	improvisation: active listening\, collaboration\, spontaneity\, and using 
	your own life experiences to create honest\, engaging scenes and stories. 
	Improv is not about being funny\, it is about being present\, supportive\,
	 and open. And yes\, along the way\, you will laugh more than you have in 
	ages. \n\nOur community values connection and growth\, and this class is b
	uilt on those principles. You will work in a supportive group where the gu
	iding philosophy is simple: When your scene partner looks good\, you look 
	good. Together\, we build trust\, confidence\, and creativity\, one scene 
	at a time. \n\nUnder the guidance of our experienced faculty\, you will le
	arn to:\n\nBe a better listener\n\nConquer fears and build confidence\n\nS
	park creativity\n\nMeet new people and make real connections\n\nBecome a b
	etter problem solver\n\nSay yes more in your life\n\nStep out of your comf
	ort zone\n\nImprove public speaking\n\nFail easier \\(and laugh about it\\
	)\n\nDiscover more about yourself\n\nHave an absolute blast\n\nThis class 
	includes lots of laughter\, lots of stage time\, and zero pressure. Every 
	student begins here. No experience needed. Just bring curiosity and a will
	ingness to try something new. \n\nUnexpected Productions Improv School is 
	thrilled to bring our newest Eastside improv classes to Issaquah\, serving
	 the communities of the Sammamish Plateau\, East Renton\, Bellevue\, Snoqu
	almie Valley\, and beyond. \n\nClass Details\n\nDates: Sundays for eight \
	\(8\\) weeks\, from March 8 to May 3\, \\(No class on April 5th\\) \n\nTim
	e: 11:00 AM to 1:00pm \n\nLocation: Improv School Eastside Issaquah \n\n13
	15 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4 Issaquah\, WA 98027 \\(next to the Gaslamp Bar
	 & Grill\\) \n\nMaximum students: 16 \n\nAges: 18 plus \n\nCost: $320 \n\n
	Prerequisite: None \n\nNote: Attendance at the first session is mandatory\
	, as it sets the tone and foundation for the entire quarter. If you know y
	ou will miss the first class\, please register for a future session. \n\nW
	hat students say\n\n“You are learning more about improv\, more about yours
	elf\, making interesting friends\, while you are learning and stretching i
	n ways that will make life better both at work and socially\, yet everyone
	 is smiling so hard your face hurts. How many stars is that worth?” \n\nJo
	nathan A.\, 5 Stars on Yelp \n\nCancellation policy\n\nThere are no refund
	s.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/intro-to-improv-eastsi
	de-issaquah-sundays/18291134/2026-03-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cultu
	re
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/intro-to-improv-eastside-
	issaquah-sundays/18291134/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:KPmH7nIznrYYxgnVpntCV
SUMMARY:Young Dragon: A Bruce Lee Story
DTSTAMP:20260307T230149Z
DTSTART:20260308T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Before he was a legend\, Bruce Lee was just a young man trying 
	to figure it all out—right here in Seattle. This action-packed\, soul-sear
	ching story follows the Young Dragon as he navigates a new country and fin
	ds his voice. Through movement\, magic\, and heart\, we meet the human beh
	ind the icon—flawed\, fierce\, and full of possibility. Watch as Lee learn
	s to clear his brain by mimicking the white noise of water and begins fusi
	ng martial arts with philosophy. From street fights in Hong Kong to teachi
	ng self-defense and chasing big dreams\, Bruce’s journey reminds us that f
	inding your way means first figuring out who you are. Come see how Seattle
	 shaped him into a flexible\, fluid\, and flowing master—and how he reshap
	ed the world.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/young-drago
	n-a-bruce-lee-story/18116297/2026-03-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cultu
	re
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/young-dragon-a-bruce-lee-
	story/18116297/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Seattle Children's Theatre\, 201 Thomas Street\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H45M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7TB-a8JLRs1kNN3IaYxkd
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260307T230149Z
DTSTART:20260308T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-03
	-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
