DTSTART:20260314T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Spend a fun-filled morning with your family learning about art 
	and the environment then get creative with a drop-in art activity led by a
	 local artist. This program takes place outside at the Olympic Sculpture P
	ark on the covered north terrace of the PACCAR Pavilion. Walk-ins welcome 
	on a first-come\, first-served basis.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/even
	ts/#/details/family-saturday/17345241/2026-03-14T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Art
	s & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/family-saturday/17345241/
	2026-03-14T00
LOCATION:Olympic Sculpture Park\, 2901 Western Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:oXW2zX0vtnpb3WIdIN0m0
SUMMARY:Samantha Yun Wall: What We Leave Behind
DTSTAMP:20260307T230149Z
DTSTART:20260314T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Samantha Yun Wall’s new paintings use overlapping silhouettes o
	f female figures as portals to unknown spaces and different temporal realm
	s. Impetus for the new body of work is a Korean folk tale in which the Pas
	que flower is symbolic of a grandmother who passed away without the loving
	 care of her grandchildren. It is a story of melancholy\, loss\, and remem
	brance. The delicate hair on the flower’s stem differentiates it\, and the
	 artist gives the plant a surreal aspect in some of her paintings\, replac
	ing the flower’s center with a watchful eye.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.c
	om/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we-leave-behind/18026187/2026-0
	3-14T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we
	-leave-behind/18026187/2026-03-14T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:KmDFpRZIgpYOLWeZA3c5v
SUMMARY:SP 202: Fabric Printing
DTSTAMP:20260307T230149Z
DTSTART:20260314T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Do you dream of people wearing your artwork out on the streets?
	 Want to make shirts for your friend’s music project? Level up your fabric
	 printing experience and take home your own printed tote bag in this 3-hou
	r intermediate-level fabric printing class! In this hands-on workshop\, yo
	u’ll explore the use-cases for printing on fabric\, practice properly sett
	ing up on the t-shirt press\, and understand different types of fabrics an
	d inks. Students will receive three tote bags to print on\, or have the op
	tion to bring their own light-colored 100% cotton fabrics to practice on. 
	Students will be printing a Vera specific design\, exclusive to the 202 cl
	ass.\n\nStudents must complete Screenprint 101 before attending this class
	.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/B75453a3bdb7\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/B75453a3bdb7
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
